        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:40PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 540 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Canisteo, or near Hornell, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Meads Creek, Keuka, Campbell, Savona, Bath, Cameron, Hammondsport,
Kanona, Urbana, and North Hornell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
